HEADWORD: Horse-leech
<hw>Horse"-leech`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A large blood-sucking leech (<spn>H⟦ae⟧mopsis
vorax</spn>), of Europe and Northern Africa. It attacks the lips and
mouths of horses.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A farrier; a veterinary surgeon.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Horse-leechery</ent>⟦br⟧
